        <h2 style="font-size: var(--fluid-h3);">What We Do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Free Town Halls:</strong> Regular in-person and online sessions where we discuss AI topics in plain language</li>
          <li><strong>Training Sessions:</strong> Hands-on workshops teaching practical AI skills for everyday life</li>
          <li><strong>Content Hub:</strong> Blog posts and videos breaking down AI concepts without the technical jargon</li>
          <li><strong>Discord Community:</strong> An ongoing space for questions, discussions, and peer support</li>
          <li><strong>Community Partnerships:</strong> Collaboration with local organizations, libraries, and schools</li>
        </ul>
        
        <div class="swiss-divider-red my-12"></div>
        <h2 style="font-size: var(--fluid-h3);">Our Approach</h2>
        <p>We believe in:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Plain Language:</strong> No jargon, no assumptions about technical knowledge</li>
          <li><strong>Reality-Based Education:</strong> Honest conversations about what AI can and can't do</li>
          <li><strong>Community-Centered:</strong> Content and sessions shaped by community needs and questions</li>
          <li><strong>Hands-On Learning:</strong> Practical demonstrations and exercises you can apply immediately</li>
          <li><strong>Inclusive Access:</strong> Free events, multiple formats, and support in multiple languages</li>
        </ul>
        
